<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sweeps Three Golds at FINA Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese divers made a
clean sweep of three gold medals at the 1998 FINA Diving Grand
Prix, by winning two more titles from the women's 10-meter
platform and the men's 3-meter springboard here Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Cai Yuyan, the 16-year-old from Guangdong province who finished
second at the World Swimming Championship last January, kept her
form through the preliminaries to collect a total of 521.55 points
to clinch the women's 10m platform title under cheers from the
enthusiastic home crowd.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Wang Yan finished second with 477.90, beating
Vyninka Arlow of Australia to third place with 475.65.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Xu Hao snatched the men's 3-meter springboard
title with 690.85 points, edging veteran Yu Zhuocheng to second
with 660.95.
</P>
<P>
Yu, winner of the 1-meter springboard and synchronized diving
at the World Swimming Championships, scored the event-high 91
points in his third dive.
</P>
<P>
Robert Newbery of Australia bagged home the bronze with 593.95.
</P>
<P>
Hu Enyong, coach of Cai Yuyan and Yu Zhuocheng, expressed his
satisfaction with the performances of his disciples, saying "both
Cai and Yu performed higher degrees of difficulty."
</P>
<P>
"However, Cai still has a lot to improve her technical skills
to ensure stable performances while Yu also lacks of systematic
training after the World Championships which explained his errors
in some dives tonight," the coach said.
</P>
<P>
The victory of Xu Hao was a reward of his supurb stability,
great sense of water and excellent techniques, although he still
has to improve his difficulty degree of the dives, his coach
commented.
</P>
<P>
Early this afternoon, Zhu Zhijia of China took the first gold
of the Grand Prix series in the women's 1-meter springboard.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
