<HEADLINE> Albanian Government Quells Riot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Albanian government troops and
police on Monday regained control of Shkoder which was overrun by
armed rioters two days ago.
</P>
<P>
The disturbance began in the northern Albanian city on Sunday
afternoon when about 50 armed men took over a local police
station, freed more than 60 criminals and set fire to offices.
</P>
<P>
The situation worsened Sunday evening with gunfire was reported
across the city. Masked mobs looted and burnt down the local court
as well as other government buildings, banks and shops.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Interior Ministry described the incident as a
"terrorist action" which was politically motivated. Some rioters
reportedly came from neighboring Montenegro.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of the National Security Committee on Monday
morning, Prime Minister Fatos Nano called on law enforcement
organisations to fight the rebels.
</P>
<P>
He vowed that the government and the Albanian people would
never submit to any criminal group and would use the rule of law
to safeguard public property and order. 
</P>
