<HEADLINE> EU to Lift Ban on High-Level Contact With Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Union agreed
Monday to resume high-level contact with Iran after the country
posted encouraging developments recently.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the 15-nation union, who met here for
a general affairs council meeting, concluded that the EU should
respond positively to the encouraging developments by increasing
the level of political contact with Iran.
</P>
<P>
As a start, the council meeting decided to resume the official
bilateral ministerial visits to explore the possibility of a new
dialogue.
</P>
<P>
EU countries recalled their diplomatic envoys for consultations
after the German court ruling but returned them last November
after resolving a stand-off over Tehran's demands that the German
ambassador return last.
</P>
<P>
Without waiting for the ban on high-level contact to be lifted,
French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine met his Iranian
counterpart, Kamal Kharrazi, in Geneva on January 29. 
