<HEADLINE> Nile Crocodile "Forgotten" by Owner in Paris Hotel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 23 (Xinhua) -- A six-month-old crocodile from
the Nile was "forgotten" by its owner in a bath tub of a Paris
hotel and has been sent to a local zoo, reported Agence
France-Press Monday.
</P>
<P>
The crocodile, 61 centimeters long, was found by a cleaner. Its
owner abandoned it probably because he was told that the crocodile
could be five meters long once it grows up, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
Marie-Claude Bomsel, professor at the National Museum of
Natural History, said that the crocodile belongs to a species
regarded as "vulnerable" by the International Union for
Conservation of Nature and is protected by the Washington
Convention on Protecting Rare Species. 
</P>
