<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Issues Congratulations to Servicemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Monday said that the Russian army and navy will accomplish
extremely important tasks of ensuring Russia's defense capability
and state security.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's remark was voiced in a message issued on the occasion
of the Day of the Fatherland's Defenders, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The president said, "Now that military reform is underway,
servicemen must display even greater professionalism, devote
themselves completely to their work and show genuine patriotism."
</P>
<P>
In the message Yeltsin noted that the state will do everything
it can to provide the armed forces with modern weapons and
equipment, and to improve the working and living conditions of the
servicemen and their families.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia may count on its defenders and believed
that state defense is in reliable hands.
</P>
<P>
On the same day Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin told
a meeting marking the Day of the Fatherland's Defenders that wages
of servicemen will be at least doubled in 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the state leaders plan to tackle the army's
social problems and have assigned sources of financing for this.
All Russian servicemen will have apartments before 2000,
Chernomyrdin promised. 
</P>
