<HEADLINE> UNDP Supplies Equipment to Indonesian Fire-Fighters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) is delivering shovels, rakes, hoses and
other equipment to Indonesia to help stamp out blazes in the
island of Sumatra, UNDP said in a press release Monday.
</P>
<P>
The fires, still burning in many places, generated smoke that
shrouded much of Southeast Asia for weeks.
</P>
<P>
Fires consumed thousands of acres of Indonesian forest last
year. UNDP's efforts are aimed at avoiding similar damage there.
</P>
<P>
UNDP said it is also delivering food, farming equipment, radio
transmitters and other emergency supplies to victims of drought on
the Indonesian island of Iryan Jaja. 
