<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Close to 8,000 Somali
refugees residing at Hartisheik in eastern Ethiopia have been
repatriated to their homeland, a report said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The stated number of refugees were repatriated in accordance
with the plan to repatriate 30,000 Somali refugees residing in
Ethiopia to Somalia voluntarily this year.
</P>
