<HEADLINE> Oman Calls Security Council to Approve Iraqi Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Oman called the
U.N. Security Council to approve the agreement signed Monday
between Iraq and U.N. Chief Kofi Annan on peaceful solution of the
Iraq-U.N. crisis on arms inspection.
</P>
<P>
The Omani news agency quoted a Foreign Ministry spokesman,
whose name was not given, as saying that Muscat hoped the agreement
"will be approved by the U.N. Security Council."
</P>
<P>
