<HEADLINE> Greek FM Hopes UN-Iraq Deal Ends Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Greek Foreign Minister
Theodoros Pangalos Monday expressed his hope that the agreement
reached by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan with Iraq would put an
end to the Iraq-U.N. standoff over arms inspection.
</P>
<P>
Pangalos made the statement here Monday morning upon the news
that Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz and the U.N. chief had
signed the deal in Baghdad on resolving the crisis peacefully.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after meeting with Egyptian President
Hosni Mubarak, the Greek diplomat accused Washington of applying
double standards in dealing with the Mideast affairs.
</P>
<P>
