that the United States dealt with various issues with double
standards," he added, referring to Mubarak's criticism of the
U.S. in an interview with CNN on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that countries will deal with other similar issues with
the same determination the Iraqi crisis was dealt with," Pangalos
added.
</P>
<P>
The Greek foreign minister said he discussed with the Egyptian
president international issues including the peace march in the
Middle East and the Iraq crisis.
</P>
<P>
Official talks between the two sides are to open Monday night
at the Foreign Ministry headquarters under the co-chairmanship of
Pangalos and his Egyptian counterpart Amr Moussa. Conditions in the
Middle East and the Balkan region are expected to top their agenda.
</P>
<P>
Pangalos, who was on a three-day visit to Egypt, arrived here
Sunday from the northern Egyptian port city of Alexandria where he
opened a photographs exhibition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
