<HEADLINE> 8 Percent of Foreign Planes in Germany Unsafe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The Federal Aviation Office in
Braunschweig reported Monday that 8 percent of foreign charter and
airline aircraft used in Germany was unsafe.
</P>
<P>
The office said that a survey conducted during the period from
May 1996 to December 1997 on 806 foreign planes found security
faults in 65 planes.
</P>
<P>
The study showed only 104 planes had no faults, 260 were
categorized as requiring improvements according to international
standards and the rest had minimal faults.
</P>
<P>
The problems ranged from thin tires, worn-down brakes, and
excess cargo and passenger weight, to leaks in the hydraulic and
fuel systems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
