<HEADLINE> UNDP to Train Experts in Disaster Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Experts from a number
of countries will receive intensive training in the new equipment
for disaster preparedness and management, the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
This is a follow-up to a recent gathering in Beijing of the
experts from 15 countries to learn how a new technique for
measuring "geomagnetic signals" can help forecast deadly storms
and earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
The technology showcased at the UNDP-hosted event will be
shared with developing countries to strengthen their early-warning
systems.
</P>
