<HEADLINE> Zambian Cabinet Reshuffled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba once again reshuffled his cabinet here Monday.
</P>
<P>
In the reshuffle, Minister of Community Development and Social
Services Samuel Miyanda was transferred to the Ministry of Lands.
</P>
<P>
Former minister of lands Chipawa Anoshi was named new minister
of communications and transport and former communications and
transport minister Dawson Lupunga was appointed new minister of
community development and social services to replace Miyanda.
</P>
<P>
He did not disclose the cause of the reshuffle.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time Chiluba reshuffled his cabinet in less
than three months.
</P>
<P>
In the reshuffle made on December 2 of 1997, the positions of
over half of his cabinet ministers were changed including vice
president and defense minister.
</P>
<P>
The sweeping shake-up came after some army officers staged a
coup on October 28 of last year but the coup was foiled by the
government forces a few hours later. 
</P>
