<HEADLINE> Commission on Population and Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The Commission on
Population and development will meet at the Headquarters from
23-27 February to address the question of health and mortality,
with special emphasis on the link between health and development
and on the issue of gender and age.
</P>
<P>
A release from the Economic and Social Council said on Monday
the Commission will examine follow-up to the recommendations of
the International conference on Population and Development, held
in Cairo in 1994, as well as preparations for a review and
appraisal process scheduled for 1999.
</P>
<P>
It will hold a general debate on national experience in
population matters, focusing on health and mortality, on which
there will be a panel discussion.
</P>
<P>
It will have before it reports of the Secretary-General on a
number of subjects, including world population monitoring in 1988
focusing on health and mortality; the monitoring of population
programmes; flows of financial resources for population
activities; and the progress of work in the field of population.
</P>
