<HEADLINE> French Communist Party Leader Hails U.N.-Iraq Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The national secretary of the
French Communist Party, Robert Hue, Monday hailed the U.N.-Iraq
agreement on arms inspection, which he said "gives credit to the
U.N. Secretary-General" and the "mobilization of opinion"
against another military intervention against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"I am delighted at the agreement because it was not clear
(what would happen) even a few days ago," he said on local
television TF1 Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
He also said that France has played an important role in
defusing the crisis by contributing to "what is written down in
the logic of peace rather than war."
</P>
<P>
"One of the lessons drawn from the current crisis is that the
power of a nation is from now on more measured by its capacity to
propose peace, the voice of diplomacy, to avoid the war rather
than make war," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
