<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientific Periodicals Need Improvement, Experts Say </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Publishing houses specializing
in scientific periodicals in China were urged today to improve the
quality of their products, so that they can gain a wider audience
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that among the country's 4,386 such
periodicals, only 0.24 percent were listed in 1993 in the American
Science Quotation Index, an important reference periodical for
basic scientific studies, and the rate dropped to 0.17 percent in
1995.
</P>
<P>
To keep up with the world trend, the publishing houses in China
should try to shorten the publication period of scientific theses,
and update the information, said an official with the publicity
department of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
He said that another factor which helps more Chinese
periodicals gain readers abroad is to offer standardized English
digests and complete references for each scientific thesis
published in periodicals.
</P>
<P>
The publishing houses of scientific periodicals have begun to
focus on publishing more outstanding scientific articles both from
at home and abroad. In 1995, Chinese periodicals carried 402 papers
written by overseas scholars; in 1996 the number rose to 539.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that group companies may be more competitive than
individual publishing houses in the world market. More than 300
scientific periodicals in the Chinese Academy of Sciences as well
as 60 periodicals in the Chinese Society of Medical Sciences are
all exploring ways for co-operation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
