<HEADLINE> Joint Genetic Research to Be Conducted in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai New Huangpu
Corporation Group and Fudan University today signed an agreement
on joint development of and research into new human gene
engineering projects.
</P>
<P>
The agreement involves 100 million yuan in investment in the
fields of cloning and the development of new human gene products.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the two sides will form a joint
venture with the New Huangpu Corporation accounting for 70 percent
of the shares, and Fudan University taking up the other 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Genetic Research Laboratory of Fudan University is China's
key institute engaged in genetic engineering research; the New
Huangpu Corporation Group is a large-sized state enterprise.
</P>
<P>
The venture will allocate funds from its pre-tax profits for
the strategic development of the biological industry in
Shanghai. 
</P>
