<HEADLINE> German Car Registrations Down in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Germany saw new car registrations
drop to 261,646 in January, 1.7 percent less than a year before,
the Federal Vehicles Office reported in Flensburg Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The office noted that total vehicle registrations came to
292,799, a drop of only 0.5 percent from January 1997, thanks to a
rise in registrations of trucks, motorcycles, tractor-trailers and
buses.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Volkswagen took the lead in private new car
registrations with 55,349, followed by Ford with 31,733. Opel came
after with 31,673, and Mercedes-Benz with 25,896. 
</P>
