<HEADLINE> Nepali Government to Formulate Agricultural Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A Nepali minister has said
that the government will formulate an agricultural plan to
increase crop production.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture Minister Prakash Chandra Lohani mentioned the plan
when addressing a regional agricultural fair and exhibition held
recently in Banke district in mid-western Nepal, the official RSS
news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But no details of the plan was disclosed, the minister only
said that the present government will making great efforts to meet
the basic needs of the farmers for fertilizers, storage and
irrigation facilities.
</P>
<P>
Lohani said though the major portion of the national income
comes from agriculture, the agricultural growth has not reached
the expected level.
</P>
<P>
Nepal was a food exporter in the 1950s, but now it is among the
79 low-income food-deficit countries in the world. 
</P>
