<HEADLINE> Number of Drug Users Surpasses 1 Million in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The number of drug users
surpassed one million in Bangladesh, although it is not a drug
producing country, Joint Secretary of Economic Relations Division
Abul Kalam Azad said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a function here, he said that the annual
consumption of drug in Bangladesh is worth over 50 billion taka
(108.7 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, he said that Bangladesh is a signatory to all
international conventions against drug abuse and trafficking and
the government has taken a five-year plan to combat the menace at
any cost.
</P>
<P>
Some 140 million people or 2.5 percent of the world population
are addicted to cannabis, known as "gaza", the national news
agency BSS said. 
</P>
