<DOCNO> XIE19980224.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> American Gerlach Wins 7th Stage of Langkawi Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 24 (Xinhua) -- American Chad Gerlach won
the seventh stage of the 1998 Le Tour de Langkawi on Tuesday but
Italian Andrea Tafi retained the yellow jersey as overall leader.
</P>
<P>
Gerlach edged Australian Peter Rogers in the final 100 meters
for the top place, while Rogers and Filipino Carlo had to settle
for the second and third places respectively.
</P>
<P>
All three recorded Gerlach's winning time of 3 hours 53 minutes
and 58 seconds in the stage which covered a distance of 176
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The eighth stage will start on Wednesday from Malacca to Port
Dickson, a popular beach resort.
</P>
<P>
About 150 riders from 24 teams were taking part in the 12-day
12-stage tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
