<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore PM Stresses Importance of Stable Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong stressed Tuesday evening the importance of the relations
between Singapore and its neighbors and said that Singapore should
help them to overcome their difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Singapore Malay Chamber of Commerce and
Industry Annual Fast-Breaking Festival Dinner, Goh said that the
political stability and economic health in the neighboring
countries are of "crucial importance" to Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The close and long-standing bilateral relations Singapore has
with Indonesia and Malaysia go beyond economics to include the
strategic, political, environmental, social and cultural areas, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"But because our interests are intertwined, problems in one
country would definitely affect the other. In short, our
relationship with Indonesia is indivisible, as is our relationship
with Malaysia," the prime minister stated.
</P>
<P>
Hence, he said, "it is neither possible nor right for us to
close our eyes or fold our arms and ignore the problems of our
neighbors. A stable and secure neighborhood is in the interests of
Singapore. We shall help our neighbors to overcome their
difficulties where we can." 
</P>
</TEXT>
