<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Set up Refineries in Europe, Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait will establish
refineries in Europe and Asia with a separate capacity of 300,000
barrels and 400,000 barrels per day (bpd) by the year 2000, Kuwait
News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Bahrain Oil and Gas News Magazine
which was published Tuesday, Kuwaiti Minister of Oil Issa
Mohammed Al-Mazidi said that Kuwait also plans to gradually expand
its marketing operations to sell 500,000 bpd of petroleum products
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
"To achieve our objectives, we are considering all sorts of
options including strategic alliances or cooperation in joint
venture projects," he said.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned conglomerate Kuwait Petroleum Corporation plans
to enter joint ventures to build and operate refineries in
India, Pakistan and Thailand, he added.
</P>
<P>
The company's long-term strategy aims to upgrade three
local refineries to reach a capacity of more than 1 million bpd
from the present 855,000 bpd.
</P>
<P>
Oil refining in the three refineries realized an increase of
about 8 percent in 1997 over the previous year, an unprecedented
record in the refineries' operations, according to official
figures.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the oil production, Al-Mazidi said "Kuwait intends
to raise production from 2.19 million bpd to 2.5 million bpd by
the end of the decade, and to 3 million bpd by the year 2005."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
