<DOCNO> XIE19980224.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Seminars Commemorate Zhou Enlai Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Several seminars were held in
Beijing today to mark the 100th anniversary of the birth of the
late Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai.
</P>
<P>
At the seminar convened by the General Office of the State
Council, some veterans who had worked with Zhou recollected his
stature as a great man and his hard-working spirit as a public
servant.
</P>
<P>
Luo Gan, secretary-general of the State Council, told the
seminar that the personal integrity and charm of Zhou Enlai are a
valuable legacy for later generations, especially in the new
historical period of building a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
He called on the departments under the General Office to seize
the opportunity of commemorating Zhou Enlai to build industrious,
honest and efficient government organs.
</P>
<P>
The United Front Work Department of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) Central Committee organized a seminar to commemorate
Zhou, inviting people from non-Communist parties, the All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce, personages with no party
affiliation and intellectuals.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the seminar noted that Zhou was the pioneer and
outstanding figure of the country's united front work. His
thinking and practice not only served as guidelines for such work
in his own time, but remain of great significance nowadays.
</P>
<P>
Despite the drastic changes in the situation and tasks which
China faces, Zhou Enlai's thinking, style of work and personal
integrity will inspire people throughout the country to advance
along the path of building a modern socialist country, the
participants said.
</P>
<P>
Peng Peiyun, state councillor and director of the State Family
Planning Commission, joined nearly 100 other population
specialists and workers in charge of family planning to
commemorate Zhou Enlai's contribution to the country's population
control work.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar held by the Office of Overseas Chinese Affairs
under the State Council, Guo Dongpo, director of the office,
called on those in charge of work connected with overseas Chinese
to learn from Zhou Enlai's lofty morality and study his
instructions on overseas Chinese affairs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, units of the People's Liberation Army and the
People's Armed Police have held various activities over the past
few days to commemorate the late Premier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980224.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Approves New Research Projects on TSE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union approved
Tuesday 22 new research projects on transmissible spongiform
encephalopathies (TSE), including mad cow disease.
</P>
<P>
The projects, totalling 21.9 million ECU (23.8 million
U.S. dollars), will focus on the transmission of the disease to
humans and new therapeutic strategies.
</P>
<P>
Ever since 1990, the European Union has been supporting
research projects on TSE.
</P>
<P>
A total of 16 projects have been launched between 1990 and
1996, but still little is known about the biology and pathology of
TSE.
</P>
<P>
The TSE illnesses form a group of fatal and transmissible
diseases which are characterised by a degeneration of the nervous
tissues both in humans and animals.
</P>
<P>
In humans they take the form of kuru, Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease
and Gerstmann-Straussler-Scheinker while degenerations found in
animals are in the form of scrapie and mad cow disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980224.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Soccer Officials Direct "Farce" in Training Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, Yunnan Province, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese
soccer officials orchestrated a "farce" on Tuesday by preventing
reporters and fans from a special national flag-raising ceremony
in the Haigeng soccer training camp, some 20 kilometers away from
the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
The flag was raised by Wang Jinyao and Cheng Jie, members of
the special detachment holding the daily flag-raising ceremony in
Tiananmen Square, which has become a must-see for tourists.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Football Association (CFA) held the ceremony as a
patriotism gesture to boost the morale of the Chinese soccer
players who are still seeking for their debut in the World Cup
finals.
</P>
<P>
Yet, some 40 reporters and fans who hurried from downtown
Kunming in the early morning were shut out from the gateline of
the training camp.
</P>
<P>
"No reason. But you are not allowed in," a CFA official said
in an arrogant tone to the reporters who showed him their
certificates of news coverage.
</P>
<P>
Another CFA official explained that the blockade was to prevent
the ceremony from being disturbed, while no incident of the kind
was ever triggered off in Tiananmen Square where hundreds of
people attended every morning, and even tens of thousands on
holidays in the flag-raising ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"It should been an honorable moment. But why do those officials
tried to make mystery of it? " a fan said in anger.
</P>
<P>
Haigeng is the training center for the Chinese national soccer
team and all the squads in Division A and B leagues during their
off-season periods.
</P>
<P>
This was the second time that the door was closed to the public
after the CFA even resorted to police dogs to prevent any outsider
in the spring of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The CFA was one of the richest sports associations in China,
yet its men footballers failed to make any impact in the
international arena while incidents of "hooligan" were reported
time and again with its most honored player involved.
</P>
<P>
Fan Zhiyi, the two-time national footballer, was caught of
punching his fan who cried for a signature in January, and kicked
the butt of his Japanese opponent on Monday in the inaugural Far
East Soccer Club Championships on his home turf in Shanghai.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
