<HEADLINE> Trade Surplus Up, Real Export and Import Down in Skorea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, February 24 (Xinhua) -- South Korea enjoyed a trade
surplus of 1.51 billion U.S. dollars last month, despite its
serious financial crisis, said the Customs administration
department on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In January, exports edged up 0.3 percent from 9.034 billion
U.S. dollars thanks largely to export of gold worth 683 million
dollars. Imports stood at 7.554 billion dollars, a drop of 39.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
However, without gold exports, January would have seen a 7.2
percent or 650-million-dollar export decline from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
South Korea suffered a trade deficit of 3.476 billion dollars
in January 1997.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is in the grip of a financial crisis triggered by
corporate failures and bad loans in late 1997. 
</P>
