<HEADLINE> Pak, Malaysia Sign Accord on Information Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Malaysia signed
an agreement here Tuesday to promote bilateral cooperation in the
field of information.
</P>
<P>
"This agreement will lay institutional basis for the
cooperation in the field of information between the two
countries," said Pakistan's Information Minister Mushahid Hussain
after he inked the document together with his visiting Malaysian
counterpart Dato Mohamed Rahmat, according to the Associated Press
of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement Pakistan and Malaysia will exchange news
programs and television drama serials as well as visits by
journalists.
</P>
<P>
National news services of the two countries -- the APP and the
Berita Nasional Malaysia -- will cooperate in the field of news
and information, the APP said.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also stipulates mutual visits of professional
officials from the information ministries of the two countries and
promotion of cooperation in the field of information technology,
especially the use of computers, said the APP.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Tuesday the two information ministers held
comprehensive discussion on promoting cooperation in the
information field between the two Muslim countries, the APP added.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers agreed to set up a joint committee to oversee
the implementation of the agreement, said the APP, adding that the
first meeting of the joint committee is scheduled to be held in
April this year in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
