<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes Anniversary Editions of Communist Manifesto </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- For purposes of commemoration
and collection, two special editions of the Communist Manifesto
have been published to mark the 150th anniversary of its
appearance.
</P>
<P>
Written jointly by Karl Marx and Friedrich Engels in February
1848, the Manifesto became the first guideline for scientific
socialism. Over the past 150 years versions have been published in
200 languages.
</P>
<P>
In China the manifesto has fostered generations of Communist
stalwarts and proletarian revolutionaries. Both Mao Zedong and
Deng Xiaoping regarded it as basic study material.
</P>
<P>
The commemoration and collection editions include facsimiles of
the front and back covers and contents pages of the first version
of the Manifesto, which was written in German language. Also, they
include reproductions of Marx's handwriting and of the front
covers of different editions produced in different countries, as
well as portraits of Marx and Engels.
</P>
<P>
There are 5,000 copies of the commemoration edition and 500
copies of the collection edition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980224.0134 </DOCNO>
