<HEADLINE> Forum Mulls Zhou Enlai's Diplomatic Ideas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 100 senior diplomats,
generals and experts on international issues gathered here today
at a forum to discuss the diplomatic ideas of the late Chinese
Premier Zhou Enlai.
</P>
<P>
Zhou was a great revolutionary, politician, military strategist
and an outstanding diplomat.
</P>
<P>
At the forum, Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of General Staff of
the People's Liberation Army, said that Zhou Enlai was the founder
of the diplomatic work of New China.
</P>
<P>
He said that Zhou from 1949 to 1976 made remarkable
contributions to China's diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
He said that Zhou's efforts raised China's status in the world,
adding that his diplomatic ideas and practice are well worth
studying.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the China Society of Administrative
Management also held a forum to commemorate the 100th anniversary
of Zhou's birth.
</P>
<P>
The forum focussed on Zhou's work at Zhongnanhai, the
headquarters of the Chinese government, in the 26 years
from 1949 to 1976.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in north China's Tianjin City, about 200,000 people
have booked tickets to visit the Museum of Zhou Enlai and Deng
Yingchao (Zhou's wife), which is to open February 28.
</P>
<P>
The museum, with a floor space of 7,150 sq m, has collected
about 8,000 historical objects and relics connected with Zhou
Enlai and Deng Yingchao, who was once chairwoman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference.  
</P>
</TEXT>
