of water, have had contacts with each other for centuries, he
said. The two nations have, since the normalization of diplomatic
ties 25 years ago, witnessed a vigorous growth of communication
and cooperation in various fields, including politics, economy,
culture and sports.
</P>
<P>
Both efforts by friendship groups and the general public, and
special promotion via nongovernmental exchanges in Japan are
responsible for the present healthy state of the relations, he
said.
</P>
<P>
