friendly ties which have been hard-earned, and hold that their
development and consolidation conform to the interests of the two
countries as well as having great significance for peace and
stability in Asia and world at large.
</P>
<P>
As long as both sides face history squarely while looking to
the future, and make joint efforts, China and Japan will surely
continue their friendship from generation to generation, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Masao Shimizu, chairman of the Japanese delegation and
vice-president of the Japan-China Friendship Association (JCFA),
thanked Li for his kind remarks, and disclosed that the JCFA will
hold a special celebration in year 2000 to commemorate its 50th
anniversary.
</P>
