<HEADLINE> Chinese Computer Industry Sees Explosive Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China's production capacity of
computers has grown 17 times since the beginning of the 1990s to
8.5 million units, according to a report by the Ministry of
Electronics Industry.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the rapid growth was caused by a demand
that has surged at more than 50 percent a year in the past seven
or eight years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, China sold 3.2 million personal computers.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the customs, education, public health and
finance sectors lead the country in adopting computers.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the report said, the taxation bureaus
nationwide had 140,000 personal computers, 14 times the figure
four years ago. 
</P>
