<HEADLINE> Book Highlights Deng's Thoughts on Scientific Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China has published a book on
Deng Xiaoping's thoughts on scientific and technological progress
to mark the first anniversary of the senior leader's death.
</P>
<P>
The book, titled, "Deng Xiaoping and Science and Technology in
China", was compiled by the China Association for Science and
Technology, the State Science and Technology Commission and other
scientific organizations.
</P>
<P>
The first part of the book contains 80 pictures of Deng
attending scientific events, most of which have never been
published before.
</P>
<P>
The second part carries 14 of Deng's articles on the
development of the country's science and technology. The book also
contains articles written by Party and state leaders on Deng's
thoughts on science and technology, as well as articles written by
leading Chinese scientists in memory of Deng.
</P>
<P>
A symposium was held in tandem with the ceremony of the
publication of the book today, hosted by major scientific
organizations in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
President of the Chinese Academy of Sciences Lu Yongxiang told
the symposium that Deng Xiaoping's thoughts on scientific and
technological development were based on analysis of the
international trends in scientific and technological development
and lessons drawn from domestic scientific work since the founding
of New China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the book will be theoretical guidance for
the realization of the strategic goals of the country's scientific
and technological development, especially that by the turn of the
century.
</P>
<P>
During the symposium officials from the State Science and
Technology Commission and the Chinese Association for Science and
Technology, and academicians from the Chinese Academy of Sciences
and the China Academy of Engineering also gave speeches to
commemorate the efforts Deng made to promote scientific and
technological development in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
