the agreement. He said he was also assured that the Americans
would make sure that the agreement fulfilled to enable peace and
stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Israel, which has been nervously observing the U.S.-Iraqi
standoff in the past weeks, breathed a sigh of relief Monday
following the signing of the Annan-Aziz agreement. But Israeli
leaders cautioned that preparation for Iraqi attack should
continue because the Gulf crisis could recur at any time.
</P>
<P>
On Israeli-Palestinian peace talks, Netanyahu said he was not
waiting for the Iraqi crisis to pass and the two sides have been
holding contacts to advance the process.
</P>
<P>
Israeli and Palestinian negotiators held a meeting in the West
Bank city Jericho on Monday, agreeing to hold regular meetings to
discuss the interim issues, including the Gaza airport, Gaza
seaport, industrial park and safe passage between West Bank and
Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
The joint negotiating teams, led separately by Israeli Cabinet
Secretary Danny Naveh and senior Palestinian negotiator Saeb
Erekat will continue the interim negotiations late Tuesday at the
residence of U.S. Ambassador Edward Walker. 
