to settle the Iraqi crisis and avert a U.S. military strike
against Iraq to force its opening up of all suspected weapons
sites to inspection.
</P>
<P>
Following a series of "difficult" talks, Annan successfully
persuaded the Iraqi leadership to comply with U.N. resolutions and
grant U.N. inspectors free and full access to all sites without
time limits. 
