<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Air Force Bombs Rebel Defense Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Ground attack aircraft of the
Sri Lanka Air Force successfully bombed the defense line of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) north of Mankulam,
Northern province, Tuesday morning, Military Spokesman Ink Dewage
said.
</P>
<P>
Dewage said the strike took place around 10:30 in the morning
along the rebel defense line parallel to the Mankulam-Olumadu
Road.
</P>
<P>
He didn't mention how many fighter planes were involved in the
strike.
</P>
<P>
Following the bombing, Mi-24 helicopter gunships engaged the
rebels at the defense line in the area, he added.
</P>
<P>
No casualties have been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
Mankulam lies some 43 kilometers north of Vavuniya, where
government troops started Operation Jayasikuru (Certain of
Victory) last may to capture the Vavuniya-Kilinochchi Road, which
connects the Jaffna peninsula to the south.
</P>
<P>
The 32-kilometer road between Mankulam and Kilinochchi and the
jungle areas on both sides of the road are under control of the
rebels.Previously the military said only 20 kilometers of the
road were left untaken by the army.
</P>
<P>
The military expects intense rebel resistance as they mount
their offensives against the rebel-held defense lines near
Mankulam. Currently the troops are only about two kilometers away
from the town. 
</P>
</TEXT>
