and Marxism-Leninism, the Communist Party of Vietnam and late
president Ho Chi Minh had persistently pursued the line of
national liberation and developed a socialist country, it said.
</P>
<P>
Learning from the experience of Vietnam's revolution over the
past 70 years and other revolutions in the world, the Communist
Party of Vietnam must take Marxism-Leninism and Ho Chi Minh's
thoughts as the ideological foundation and lodestar of its
activities to continue the renewal process, the editorial noted.
