<HEADLINE> Visitors Flock to Lei Feng Memorial Hall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A total of 41 million
visitors have passed through the Lei Feng Memorial Hall since
it was built 30 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Lei Feng was a model Chinese soldier who died in an accident at
the age of 23 in 1965. The hall is located in Fushun, in northeast
China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Lei Feng became famous for his selfless care for others and
his readiness to help the needy, and was set up as an example for
all Chinese people to follow.
</P>
<P>
Admission to the memorial hall, covering an area of 4,400 sq m,
is free of charge, and it is open every day of the year.
</P>
<P>
A wedding ceremony was held for eight couples at the
hall last September.
</P>
<P>
Some visitors consider it a holy place for purifying the
spirit, and some feel a burst of confidence as soon as they enter
the hall, according to comments in its visitors' book.
</P>
<P>
Exhibitions on the glorious deeds of Lei Feng have also been
sponsored by the memorial hall around the province; an exhibition
tour of 14 cities across the province last year attracted 70,000
viewers. 
</P>
