<HEADLINE> Cayard Wins Fifth Leg in Round-the-world Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- American skipper Paul Cayard
steered the Swedish boat EF Language to victory on the fifth leg
of the Whitbread Round the World Race in Sao Sebastiao, Brazil, on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Cayard crossed the finish line in Sao Sebastiao at nine minutes
past midnight local time to register the boat's third win in the
five legs so far.
</P>
<P>
The San Francisco-based skipper and his crew, who also won the
first and third legs, completed the 6,670-mile journey from
Auckland in 23 days one hour nine minutes and 23 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Roy Heiner's Dutch entry Brunel Sunergy finished second with
some 508 miles behind, it is expected that this will turn out to
be a record margin for a Whitbread Race leg victory. 
