<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports January Auto Production Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China manufactured 100,700
automobiles in January, down 18.21 percent on the 1997 period,
according to statistics released by the auto production department
under China's Ministry of Machine-Building Industry.
</P>
<P>
A total of 88,400 automobiles were sold during the month, down
22.84 percent on January 1996.
</P>
<P>
Some 125,600 automobiles remained in inventory at the end of
the month.
</P>
<P>
Industry analysts attribute the decrease in production and
sales to fewer work days in January, with holidays for both New
Year's Day and the Chinese Lunar New Year which commenced on
Jan. 28.
</P>
<P>
However, production and sales of mini-buses grew slightly
during the month, with the 17,600 units rolling off the assembly
line representing 0.44 percent growth on the previous year's
period.
</P>
<P>
Sales of mini-buses grew one percent to 17,400 units.
</P>
<P>
The respective production volumes for heavy-duty, medium-weight
and light-weight trucks stood at 1,700, 9,400 and 16,800
respectively, with corresponding sales volumes ending at 1,300,
6,800 and 13,100 units.
</P>
<P>
The sector manufactured 33,000 automobiles and sold 30,200 units
during the month.
</P>
<P>
Various automobiles manufacturers enjoyed rising production and
sales, including First Automotive Works (FAW)-Volkswagen and
FAW-Jinbei. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
