<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> b d e   BC-China-Iron &AMP; Steel-January China's Iron, Steel Production Grows Steadily in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China produced 8.77 million
tons of steel in January, an increase of 6.5 percent over the
year-ago period, according to statistics released by China's
Ministry of Metallurgical Industry.
</P>
<P>
This was only one of China's major iron and steel products that
achieved steady growth.
</P>
<P>
During the month, the production volume of pig iron reached
9.04 million tons, up 6.3 percent; that of rolled steel was 7.26
million tons, up 4.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, coke and ferro-alloy production exceeded demand. The
production volume of coke dropped 2.4 percent from the same period
last year, and ferro-alloy, 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The impact of Southeast Asia's financial crisis on the
international rolled steel market has put pressure on China's
exports of iron and steel products, according industry analysts.
</P>
<P>
This resulted in a 41 percent decline for the same period last
year in China's exports of billet and rolled steel in January,
which totaled 270,000 tons. Merely 60,000 tons of billet was
exported, a decrease of 71 percent.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say with the intensifying domestic market competition,
prices for major products are steadily declining.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
