<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Projections Call for Surging Rural Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China's rural market is
expected to flourish in 1998, with projections calling the rural
consumer goods retail volume to hit 1,354.3 billion yuan, up 13
percent on 1997, according to a report released by the State
Information Center.
</P>
<P>
The report indicates that rural markets will witness varying
margins of demand for various types of consumer goods, with
particularly brisk sales expected for household appliances,
including color television sets, refrigerators and washing
machines.
</P>
<P>
Demand for pesticides, plastic sheeting and fertilizer is also
expected to rise as farmers increase investments in production.
Balanced supply and demand for most agricultural capital goods,
with the exception of diesel fuel and some farm machinery, will
most likely be maintained this year under conditions featuring
increased supplies and stable prices.
</P>
<P>
Some 10 percent of housing in rural areas will be rebuilt or
refurbished during the Ninth Five-Year Plan Period (1996-2000).
The report indicates that 72 billion yuan in capital will be
earmarked for refurbishing housing with floor space of over 400
million square meters.
</P>
<P>
The rapid development of the rural market in recent years
readily indicates the vast potential for further expansion, and an
increasing number of commercial and industrial enterprises are
basing their marketing goals on rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Based on the preconditions of adjusting product mix, lowering
production costs and guaranteeing quality, state-owned enterprises
will develop practical products targeting rural consumers, while
enterprises under various forms of ownership will compete in terms
of pricing and other functional areas beyond simply solidifying
and expanding existing markets.
</P>
<P>
The rural market will witness increasing competition coupled
with expanded production and increased supplies of commodities,
according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
