<HEADLINE> ESCAP Ministers Urge Strengthening Competitiveness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Asian countries should
maintain the region's vast potential of industrial and
technological dynamism by promoting industrial competitiveness and
complementarities in manufacturing, ministers said at the end of
the two-day ESCAP meeting Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ministers of industry and technology from 25 members and
associate members of the United Nations Economic and Social
Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP) issued a declaration
and a regional action plan on strengthening regional cooperation
for industry and technological development.
</P>
<P>
In the declaration, the ministers urged ESCAP members to
promote dialogues between policy makers, experts as well as
private and public sectors to strengthen industrial restructuring
and technological development, so as to improve competitiveness
and complementarities in manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Declaration also called for more investment in
human resources and information transfer.
</P>
<P>
The Regional Action Plan gave detailed proposals to promoting
investment-related technology transfer, private sector development
and skills development for sustained industrial and technological
development in ESCAP Region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
