<HEADLINE> Sanya-Hong Kong Cruise Route Resumes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A luxurious pleasure boat, the
"Shuangyuxing" of Singapore, resumed its service between Hong Kong
and Sanya, a tropical tourist resort on Hainan Island.
</P>
<P>
The cruise ship, capable of accommodating 1,900 passengers,
offers a weekly round trip between Hong Kong and Sanya.
</P>
<P>
Tourists taking the ship to Sanya can participate in a
three-day round-the-island cruise organized by the Hainan Branch
of China International Travel Service.
</P>
<P>
The ship, believed to be the largest of its kind in Asia,
started the route in June of 1995, but the service was quickly
halted.
</P>
<P>
Since Sanya is drawing more and more tourists, Star Cruises
Ltd. decided to resume the trip after talking with relevant
departments of Sanya. 
