<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Dissolves Trust Investment Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China
(PBOC) today officially announced disbandment of the China
Agricultural Trust and Investment Company (CATIC).
</P>
<P>
The announcement said PBOC disbanded CATIC according to law on
January 4, 1997, and assigned custodial responsibility to the
China Construction Bank.
</P>
<P>
CATIC's securities section will be incorporated in the China
Xinda Trust Investment Company, with the latter assuming control
of specified assets and liabilities.
</P>
<P>
The China Construction Bank will assume all other assets and
debts, excluding those transferred to the Ministry of Finance, the
Agricultural Bank of China and the Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
China Construction Bank will carry out required legal
procedures as the creditor and will assume control of the
headquarters and financial branches of the former CATIC.
</P>
<P>
CATIC's huge losses and inability to pay its debts were
attributed to illegal business practices uncovered in 1997. The
PBOC responded by dissolving the company to protect national
financial order and the rights of creditors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
