<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Modern Skiing Facility Built in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The largest skiing
facility in north China was officially opened here after six days
of trial operation.
</P>
<P>
Located in the Saihanba Forest Park in Weichang county, 350
 kilometers north of Beijing, the skiing facility has three
courses. One course with a slope of seven degrees is designed for
beginners, and the other two with a slope of 15 degrees are for
more skillful skiers.
</P>
<P>
The attraction, covering two million square meters, is equipped
with two cables imported from France and 200 sets of skiing
equipment bought in Japan and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
It is favorably located in the Mulan Hunting Ground, a tourist
resort popular with people from Beijing, Tianjin and other cities
in north China. The snow, which usually starts in October, is as
thick as 50 centimeters, and lasts until May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
