<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minister Urges Greater Efforts for Information Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China should exert greater
efforts to develop its information industry to boost economic
growth, said Hu Qili, minister of Electronics Industry.
</P>
<P>
Today's People's Daily quoted Hu as saying that "the level of
economic information has emerged an important gauge of a country's
comprehensive national strength."
</P>
<P>
"Developing the information industry and using electronic
information technology to boost economic growth is highly
realistic and will have far-reaching significance," Hu said.
</P>
<P>
Hu noted that the Chinese Government has attached great
importance to development of the information industry in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the 1997 output value for the electronics
industry hit 380 billion yuan, a 3.8-fold rise on 1992, with the
sales volume growing by 3.2-fold to 250 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The electronics industry grew by an average 27.5 percent
annually between 1992-1997, the highest rate for all industries,
according to Hu.
</P>
<P>
He said that China faces serious challenges in terms of
developing its electronics industry.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate for electronic information technology will
exceed that of the past 10-20 years, said Hu, adding that the
industry is expected to achieve major breakthroughs in computers,
telecommunication, broadcasting and display technology.
</P>
<P>
"We face challenges in terms of grasping opportunities economic
digitalization and networking offer for upgrading the industrial
mix," according to the minister.
</P>
<P>
Projections call for the electronic information market to soar
to one trillion yuan by the year 2000, with the figure expected to
rise to six trillion yuan by 2010.
</P>
<P>
"The market will emerge as a major driving force in China's
economic growth," said Hu.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China enjoys many favorable conditions for
developing the electronics information industry, and the Chinese
market will open further and gain increasing competitiveness in
terms of supply and demand.
</P>
<P>
The Minister called for the introduction of strategic measures
to promote the shift from simulation to digitalized technology,
and noted simulated electronic products are rapidly being replaced
by digitalized products.
</P>
<P>
He called for greater efforts to raise the level of economic
information and wider use of electronic information technology in
the transformation of traditional industries.
</P>
<P>
In terms of applications, development of the software, chip
design and integrated circuit industries fully conforms to
national conditions, said Hu.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
