<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lien Chan's Activities in Middle East Denounced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China today urged some
countries to set store by the overall interests of bilateral
relations and keep vigilant against the political scheme of the
Taiwan authorities and refrain from doing anything that will hurt
the feelings of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao made the remark
here today at a regular press conference when asked to comment on
activities conducted by Lien Chan from Taiwan in Jordan and some
other Mideast countries.
</P>
<P>
"We are deeply concerned over this," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the question of Taiwan is a major and sensitive
matter of principle that bears upon China's sovereignty and
unification and touches on the feelings of the 1.2 billion Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
"We take no objection to the non-governmental contacts between
countries concerned and Taiwan, but we are firmly opposed to any
forms of governmental contacts with Taiwan by countries having
diplomatic relations with China," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu went on to say that the Taiwan authorities, by capitalizing
on the temporary economic difficulties of some countries, have
been pursuing "pragmatic diplomacy" by means of offering so-called
"economic assistance" and conducting "economic cooperation" in an
attempt to undermine friendly relations between China and
countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
"This is something the Chinese government and people can never
tolerate," he stated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
