<HEADLINE> Malaysia Hopes UN-Iraq Deal Acceptable to All Parties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Tuesday
expressed the hope that the accord reached Monday between the
United Nations and Iraq pertaining to the dispute over weapons
inspections in Iraq would be acceptable to all parties.
</P>
<P>
"We are relieved that an agreement has been concluded" between
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan and Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister
Tareq Aziz, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said when
