may be wrong," he said.
</P>
<P>
To another question concerning whether U.N. economic sanctions
against Iraq should be removed following the latest development,
he said he hoped the sanctions could be lifted.
</P>
<P>
"But I feel there will be other excuses for not lifting the
economic sanctions," he said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Monday, Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Badawi said
Malaysia welcomed the U.N.-Iraq agreement "with joy."
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is among the countries that felt that the issue should
be settled through diplomacy and not military strikes.  
