<HEADLINE> Stocks Plunge in Tokyo on Poor Economic Outlook </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stocks tumbled Tuesday on
despair over Japan's poor economic outlook, spurred by pessimistic
earnings projections for the current business year.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First section
at the Tokyo Stock Exchange plunged 411.49 points, or 2.48
percent, from Monday to close at 16,198.00.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, declined 19.81 points, or 1.58
percent, to 1,234.77.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section grew to an estimated 360 million
shares from Monday's 320.87 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Failed Yamaichi Securities was Tuesday's most heavily traded
issue.
</P>
<P>
Trading remained lacklustre most of the day on the final day
for February delivery, but selling to clear positions for the
month increased just before the market closed, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,329 issues listed on the First Section, losers
outweighed gainers 908 to 208 with 136 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
