<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Textile Export Volume up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China's textiles and garments
export volume reached 45.45 billion U.S. dollars last year, up 22.8
percent over the previous year, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The figure accounts for one-fourth of the country's total
export volume, according to the China National Textiles Import and
Export Corp.
</P>
<P>
Last year also witnessed imports of 13.33 billion U.S. dollars
worth of textiles and garments, up 3.13 percent.
</P>
<P>
The product mix of China's textile industry underwent great
change during the year. Garments and their complementary
businesses accounted for 70 percent of the total textile
exports. Processing trade has become a major pattern for export.
</P>
<P>
Besides the United States and Japan, two major overseas markets
of Chinese textiles, the country expanded its exports to the
members of the Commonwealth of Independent States and African
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
