<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Close Slightly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell 1.87
points, or 0.02 percent, to close at 10,683.34 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Shares of commerce and industry and properties dropped by 1.04
percent and 0.20 percent respectively while shares of finance and
utilities rose respectively by 0.67 percent and 0.16 percent.
</P>
<P>
H shares, namely China State-Owned Enterprises listed on the
Hong Kong bourse, went up by 8.83 percent while red chips
increased by 3.67 percent.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's turnover was 8,055 million HK dollars (1,033 million
U.S. dollars), a rise of 1,003 million HK dollars (129 million
U.S. dollars) from the previous trading day.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index opened at 10,740.82 in the morning, an
increase of 55.61 points or 0.52 percent from the close of the
previous trading day.
</P>
<P>
The shares dropped 92.56 points, or 0.87 percent, to close at
10,592.65 at midday Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The stocks went up 85.42 points, or 0.81 percent to close at
10,685.21 on Monday. 
