<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province Makes Breakthrough in Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu
Province had a total import and export volume of 546 million U.S.
dollars in 1997. Its 407 million U.S. dollars of exports were a
record high for the province.
</P>
<P>
Gansu added 28 enterprises with export rights in 1997. The
province now has 100 enterprises with export rights.
</P>
<P>
Those enterprises with export rights, together with
overseas-funded enterprises, have completed 244 million U.S.
dollars of exports, over half of the province's total export
volume in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Last year Gansu had three enterprises with exports exceeding 40
million U.S. dollars each, and 13 enterprises with exports of at
least 10 million U.S. dollars each. 
