<HEADLINE> ARATS Calls for Political Negotiations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Association for Relations
Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) sent a letter to the Taiwan
Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) today, calling for political
negotiations between the two sides across the Straits.
</P>
<P>
The letter noted that political negotiations will help improve
and develop relations between the two sides. ARATS is willing to
join SEF in discussing procedural matters of political
negotiations and will thereafter arrange reopening talks on both
economic and routine issues.
</P>
<P>
ARATS also advocates further expanding exchanges and contacts
with SEF in advance of negotiations.
</P>
<P>
ARATS issed a news release on November 11 last year. In
addition, ARATS received letters from SEF on November 7, 1997, and
January 19, 1998.
</P>
<P>
In today's letter ARATS welcomes SEF Chairman Koo Chen-fu to
visit inland areas at an appropriate time. Officials from the two
organizations may make necessary preparations for the visit during
the exchange of their visits, the letter said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
