<HEADLINE> Mingsheng Bank Opens Branch in Taiyuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China Minsheng Banking Corp.,
the country's first share-holding bank by private businesses,
opened a branch in Taiyuan, capital of north China's Shanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The branch is the bank's first in the central and western part
of China, which will provide banking services to private
enterprises in the region, said Yao Fang, director of Minsheng's
Taiyuan branch.
</P>
<P>
The bank will also pool funds and provide financial support
that will help accelerate reform of local state-owned enterprises,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Mingsheng is the first commercial bank approved by the State
Council and the People's Bank of China and was jointly funded by
private business people two years ago.
</P>
<P>
The bank mainly provides financial services to non-state
economies, townships and foreign-funded enterprises. It has
established branches in Beijing, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Wuhan and
Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
