<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Tourism Group Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Tourism Group Co
Ltd was established here yesterday, with the goal of becoming a
comprehensive transnational tourism group within three years.
</P>
<P>
The Group consists of 108 economic entities, including hotels,
travel agencies, transportation bodies, restaurants, real estate
development firms and advertising companies. The Beijing Hotel and
the Great Wall Hotel are also subsidiaries of the Group.
</P>
<P>
With total assets valued at 10.7 billion yuan (about one
billion US dollars), the group will expand its business to the
fields of aviation, electronic telecommunications and finance.
</P>
<P>
The capital city's tourism industry has been developing rapidly
in recent years, with the income from this field accounting for 40
percent of its tertiary industry.
</P>
<P>
The income of the city's tourism industry reached 39 billion
yuan last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
