<HEADLINE> Yunnan Preparing for Horticulture Fair Scheduled for Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 300 million yuan has
been spent on the construction of halls and booths for the '99
Kunming International Horticulture Fair, according to local
sources.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which will cover 200 ha, is scheduled to be held in
this capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province from May to
October 1999.
</P>
<P>
The fair, the only large international event China's central
government will host before the turn of this century, is expected
to receive eight million to 10 million visitors. It is expected to
cost a total of 1.64 billion yuan (about 200 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
So far, 70 percent of the infrastructure has been completed,
with the main facilities for indoor exhibition halls finished and
work on outdoor exhibition booths being carried out energetically.
</P>
<P>
According to the schedule, the related civil engineering and
horticultural projects should be finished by the end of this year,
and the entire preparatory work should be completed before March
1999. 
</P>
