<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cheetahs Cubs Alive and Well With Dog Milk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Zookeepers at the Shanghai
Safari Park are raising 11 orphaned African cheetah cubs with the
help of a surrogate mother.
</P>
<P>
The mother, which produced two litters of cubs over a 100 day
period in 1997, died soon after birth of the second
litter. Zookeepers explored numerous options and opted for a dog
to serve as the surrogate mother. The decision was based on the
fact that milk produced by a female dog contains the same immunity
factors as that of a female cheetah.
</P>
<P>
The healthy cubs have survived several months on a regimen of
nursing and food additives provided by zookeepers.
</P>
<P>
This marks the first time Chinese zookeepers have raised
African cheetah cubs in captivity. However, the park purchased 10
cheetahs in July 1996 and has since raised them in a
60,000-sq.m. enclosure.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai City Tribune recently donated 60,000 yuan to care
for cubs. The generous donation is expected the raise public
awareness of the need for wildlife protection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
