<HEADLINE> Olympic Flag Arrives at Salt Lake City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,500 people
welcomed the Salt Lake Olympic Organizing Committee members back
from Japan with the Olympic flag for the next Winter Olympic Games
at the city in 2002.
</P>
<P>
Salt Lake City mayor Deedee Corradini was presented with the
flag at the closing ceremonies in Nagano, Japan, and an honor
guard unfurled it Monday after the delegation's plane landed at
the Salt Lake City.
</P>
<P>
The white flag with the five Olympic rings will be placed in a
vault until 2002.
</P>
<P>
San Francisco 49ers quarterback Steve Young was the master of
ceremonies at the airport. Four U.S. Olympic medal winners,
including freestyle skiing gold winner Eric Bergoust, came back
from Nagano with the Salt Lake delegation.
</P>
<P>
Salt Lake had been denied the Winter Games three times, losing
to Sapporo, Japan in 1972, Innsbruck, Austria in 1976 and
Nagano. 
</P>
