<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
settled down on Tuesday from the power crisis in Auckland. The
major market indicator rose on the back of gains in Telecom
shares.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 8 points higher at 2,267 with a turnover
of 68 million dollars (39 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares jumped 15 cents to 815 cents. Other higher
leaders included Air New Zealand, gaining 4 cents to 204 cents,
Brierley Investment and Fletcher Paper, each up 1 cent to 113
cents and 223 cents respectively, and Lion Nathan, rising 6 cents
to 418 cents.
</P>
<P>
The main leaders to weaken were Carter Holt Harvey, down 2
cents to 270 cents and Fletcher Energy, diving 13 cents to 636
cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 41 rises and 40 falls.  
</P>
