<HEADLINE> Milosevic, U.S. Envoy Hold Talks on Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic met United States envoy Robert Gelbard Monday to
exchange views on the implementation of the Dayton agreement and
other issues regarding the peace process in the region.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have agreed that the Bosnian Serb government is
making an effort to improve economic and political conditions. The
stable operation of the government is important to the nation's
unity and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Both of them maintained that further enhancement of bilateral
relations between Yugoslavia and the United State would be
beneficial to the common interests of the two countries, and help
strengthen the peace process and stability of the region.
</P>
