<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Foreign Exchange Reserves up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's foreign exchange
reserves have risen to 1.83 billion U.S. dollars after a
staggering decline over the past year, press reports said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The amount was registered on February 18, showing an upward
trend, the country's central bank, the Bangladesh Bank, was quoted
as saying on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The country's foreign exchange reserves were 1.71 billion
dollars at the end of June 1997, and slightly rose to 1.73 billion
dollars at the end of January 1998.
</P>
<P>
The bank attributed the increase in foreign exchange reserves
to growing export earnings and remittance of Bangladeshi wage
earners in other countries.
</P>
<P>
It hoped to further boost the reserves to 2 billion dollars at
the end of June. 
</P>
