<HEADLINE> China's Light-Industry Output Value Rises 13 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China's light industry
produced 5.37 trillion yuan worth of output in 1997, an increase
of 13 percent over 1996, according to a report by the China
National Council of Light Industry.
</P>
<P>
Light industry overtook heavy industry by 1.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the light industry sector had an added value of
885.5 billion yuan in 1997, a rise of 11.5 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
Output of air conditioners, soft drinks, washing machines,
dairy products, refrigerators, beer and other products grew at
rates ranging from 10.3 percent to 25.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Output declined for 11 light-industry products such as
newsprint, electric fans, bicycles and thin plastics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
