<HEADLINE> Honduras Ready to De-limit Sea Borders with Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Honduras is preparing to
place the first marker buoy in the Fonseca Gulf in order to
facilitate negotiations with Nicaragua over a long-standing
dispute regarding territorial fishing rights, Honduran Foreign
Minister Fernando Martinez said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Gulf of Fonseca, a bay on the Pacific coast of Central
America, is an important area for catching sharks, which are
hunted for their livers.
</P>
<P>
Honduras, Nicaragua and El Salvador have been in dispute for
years over territorial waters in the gulf.
</P>
<P>
Martinez said that de-limiting shared waters has to be done
bilaterally rather than unilaterally.
</P>
<P>
He said he is to meet his Nicaraguan counterpart, Emilio
Alvarez, Thursday to further discuss the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
