U.N., the Spanish minister said that Annan's success "has brought
us onto a correct way to get out of the crisis."
</P>
<P>
Annan arrived in Baghdad Friday evening in what is believed to
be the last-ditch effort to seek a peaceful solution to the
standoff between the United States and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference in Baghdad Monday, the U.N. Chief
confirmed that an agreement had been concluded with the Iraqi
authorities. 
