<HEADLINE> Bruguera Fails while Ivanisevic Triumphs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Spanish sixth seed Sergi
Bruguera crashed out of the London indoor tennis tournament on
Monday while the big-serving Croatian Goran Ivanisevic sailed
through on the speedy court.
</P>
<P>
The former French Open champion, overpowered by Dutch Jan
Siemerink's serve, went down 6-1, 7-6 (7-3).
</P>
<P>
Eighth seed Ivanisevic took just 45 minutes to seal victory
against Dane Kenneth Carlsen 6-1, 6-2 with 13 powerful aces.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian said the speedy court fit him well and it was an
easy victory.
</P>
<P>
Siemerink will face Czech Bohdan Ulihrach in the second round,
while Ivanisevic meets the winner of Tuesday's match between
British qualifier Chris Wilkinson and South African Wayne
Ferreira.
</P>
<P>
Australian Open champion Petr Korda and U.S. Open champion Pat
Rafter head the seedings for the tournament which also includes
top Briton Greg Rusedski, seeded fourth and Russia's Yevgeny
Kafelnikov at number three. 
