<HEADLINE> Stafford Beats Seventh-seeded Fromberg in First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Grant STafford of South
Africa upset seventh-seeded Richard Fromberg 7-6 (7-4), 7-6 (7-4)
in the first round of the Advanta Championships at Philadelphia on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Stafford, who is ranked No. 67 in the world, beat the
42nd-ranked Australian Fromberg with a solid return game.
</P>
<P>
In the first set, Stafford once led at 4-1. Fromberg fought
back to take the match into tie-breaker. But it was Stafford who
controlled the tie-breaker which he ended with an ace.
</P>
<P>
In the second-set tiebreaker, Stafford took command by winning
three consecutive points after the score were levelled at 2-2. He
went on to win the tie-breaker and the match.
</P>
<P>
In other first round matches, Spain's Juan Albert Viloca
defeated Fernando Meligeni of Argentina 7-6 (7-5), 6-4 and Davide
Sanguinetti of Italy beat his compatriot Andrea Gaudenzi 5-7, 6-4,
6-3. 
</P>
