<HEADLINE> U.S. Pensions, Employee Benefits Amount to $5 Trillion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 23 (Xinhua) -- The funds held in the U.S.
pensions, retirement plans and charitable foundations and
endowments grew by over 10 percent in 1997 to nearly 5.1 trillion
U.S. dollars, a survey shows.
</P>
<P>
Of these tax-exempt pools of capital, retirement funds and
related employee benefits make up some 86 percent, with charitable
foundations and endowments comprising the remainder, according to
a report released by Nelson Information, Inc. on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The gap between the U.S. national debt amounting to 5.6
trillion dollars in late January and the pension assets fell to
560 billion dollars from 760 billion dollars in 1996, said Nelson,
citing official figures.
</P>
<P>
Nelson is a leading provider of information to financial
professionals and individuals in the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
