<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 23 (Xinhua) -- Technology shares pushed the
Nastaq index to its record high on Monday but the broad market
ended mixed with the Dow Jones industrial average edging down 3.74
points to 8,410.20.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nastaq index rose 23.63 to 1,751.76 with
computer-related companies such as Microsoft, Dell Computer and
Intel being the biggest gainers.
</P>
<P>
Nastaq stocks bettered its previous record closing of 1,745.70
set on October 9, 1997.
</P>
<P>
On other market measures, the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock list
rose 3.93 to 1,038.14 and the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE)
composite index rose 0.92 to 538.41.
</P>
<P>
On the smaller companies' front, the Russell 2000 index gained
2.30 to 456.29, but the American Stock Exchange composite index
fell 0.11 to 689.08.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues beat decliners 10-9 on NYSE, with 1,557 up,
1,426 down and 489 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Transaction volume amounted to 549.96 million shares down from
591.59 million shares previously. 
</P>
</TEXT>
