<HEADLINE> Chirac Gives Personal Touch in Welcoming Annan from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 23 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
gave a personal touch Monday night in welcoming the United Nations
Secretary-General Kofi Annan back triumphant from Baghdad with a
deal in his hand which has been hailed by many, and supported by
the U.S. President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
"Bravo!" said Chirac when receiving Annan at the Elysee
presidential palace, where they had an informal dinner during
which he treated Annan with bass, grilled chicken, ice cream, and
Bordeaux wine, with French foreign minister and other top
diplomats present.
</P>
<P>
When they ended the dinner, Chirac accompanied Annan to his car
parked in the courtyard of the presidential palace, and wished him
good night at the Crillon Hotel palace in downtown Paris prepared
for him by the French government.
</P>
<P>
None of them made any official statement, and Chirac only said
half-jokingly that he was more optimistic tonight than last night.
</P>
</TEXT>
